<br>
A Mage can really only easily deal with a single add.    And the Mage's only real option (there are some Earthpet tricks, but I won't get into them here, they are difficult to do) is to kill the add.   Mainly by putting a pet on it and Chain casting Nukes, Pets, or combination thereof to kill it fast.<br>
<br>
Still, it is rather impressive from a sheer damage-in-a-short-time persepective.   I can usually take whatever mob my group is dealing with, alone, whilst they fight the other.   But normally, I just sic the pet on the add to keep it busy, and then help the group via nukes with the original mob.   That is about the extent of a Mage's crowd control in a nutshell.   Better to have an Enchanter, Bard, Necro, or even a Cleric or Druid with harmony/lull/soothe/root/fear/snare/stun type spells do the crowd control then depend on a Mage to use the pet to hold/kill one or more extra mobs.<br>
<br>
As for soloing -- both classes do it well.   I would not make that your primary distinction.   Necro can often solo things earlier (and break camps much easier), and Mages can clear out massive low blues at an incredible rate.   Both can solo big stuff with lots of health at different points in the career.<br>
<br>
One thing Haemonculus intentionally understates is Mage damage potential...when he said &quot;Oh yeah baby, that 825dmg nuke (Assuming you're level 57+) is just raping the @#%$ out of those MoBs with over 20k hps.&quot;   I think he means that you are not going to make a dent in such critters.  Consider pet chain casting combines with nukes, and even rain spells outdoors...<br>
<br>
57 Mage, chain casting 49, or 51 earth pets, focused, ~2.5K to 3K health each.   Damage shielded, the Mage could probably chain 10,12 or more of these in a row, medding in the middle.  A 30K meat shield essentially, if you want to take big bad mob down slow.<br>
<br>
Or chain less pets and nuke with Sirocco for 640 for 3 waves, 1920 damage per cast if all hit, especially in Velious, low fire resists there.  7.5sec cast time.  One Sirocco has the potential here to do 10% damage to 20Khpts mob.    Perhaps also season your rain with some Scars of Sigil's, a 450 hit point spell, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 2.0 second cast time</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, a pure machine gun, 175 mana a pop.    Man, I can't wait for these spells <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Adding all this damage:  Pet Melee + Damage Shield + Rains + Scars, I think this is quite a bit better then just making it seem like a Mage only is casting Shock of Steel every 6-10 seconds.  You might not do 20K in 30 seconds, but in about 90 seconds the Mage could have the thing half dead or more.  Alone.<br>
